records.addlTxt:
Defendant Shannon M Stelloh in court with student intern, Mr. Schuyler Boggio, under the Student Practice Rule and with the supervision of attorney Melissa J. Fitzsimmons.  Deann L. Heard appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.

AS TO COUNT 01:
Court imposed but stayed 9 months at the House of Correction; Huber and good time allowed, and placed defendant on two years probation. Credit for 6 days time served.

AS TO COUNT 02:
Court imposed but stayed 2 months at the House of Correction, consecutive to Count 1, Huber and good time allowwed, and placed defendant on two years probation, concurrent to Count 1.

AS TO COUNT 03:
Court imposed but stayed 3 months at the House of Correction, consecutive to Count 2, Huber and good time allowed, and placed defendant on two years probation, concurrent to Count 2.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION FOR COUNTS 1, 2 AND 3:
 - Undergo a mental health evaluation; follow thru with any treatment recommended, including any medication regimen;
 - No controlled substances other than those legally prescribed for defendant by a duly licensed physician for her mental or physical well-being; take as prescribed and only for as long as deemed medically reasonable and necessary;
 - No alcohol;
 - Urine screens;
 - AODA assessment; treatment if needed;
  - Court imposed but stayed 60 days condition time as to Count 1 only, to be used for any violations;
 - Anger management counseling;
 - Parenting classes/counseling;
 - Cognitive thinking intervention counseling;
 - Seek and maintain employment;
 - Be given job and vocational training;
 - No contact with the Wal Mart at 6701 South 27th Street, city of Franklin, county of Milwaukee;
 - Pay $11.50 restitution to Wal Mart; pay $899.43 to Accident Fund Holdings; Court reserves its right regarding any possible additional monies due and owing to be set at another date.  Pay the DNA surcharge, costs and disbursements.  Failure to pay would result in a civil judgment entered against defendant which is non-dischargable in bankruptcy.

Court set restitution hearing on 8/11/14 at 8:30 a.m. 

Filed,
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
Pretrial Incarceration Credit.
